BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ayRBkoIgY4Ipaly67sCIY
SUMMARY:Scandinavian Showcase with an Irish Twist presented by Seattle Folk
	lore Society & Skandia
DTSTAMP:20260317T050002Z
DTSTART:20260321T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Mira\\\, Elise & Pat perform traditional Nordic fiddle tunes th
	at transport listeners and dancers to far-off lands real and imagined. Mir
	a Dickey (hardingfele and fiddle)\\\, Elise Snoey (fiddle and hardingfele)
	\\\, and Patrick Gunning (guitars and fiddle) bring vibrant harmonies and 
	driving groove to timeless music. Sølvstål | Silversteel is a new project 
	from hardanger fiddle player Mira Dickey and viola d’amore and fiddle play
	er Lennart Jansson exploring the novel musical territory at the intersecti
	on of Norwegian fiddling and Irish traditional music.   \\nSFS and Skandia
	 Folkdance Society are thrilled to co-sponsor and showcase 2 local Scandin
	avian music bands for this concert. These dynamic young performers have a 
	way of bringing the music to life!  \\nThe doors open at 7 pm for the 7:30
	 pm concert in the Community Hall (lower Brick building).  \\nAdvance tick
	ets available now\\\, $2 more for adults at the door. (Discounts for SFS\\
	\, PNA\\\, & Skandia members\\\, students\\\, seniors 65+/ special $10 pri
	ce for youth up to 17)\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/scandinavian
	-showcase-with-an-irish-twist-presented-by-seattle-folklore-society-skandi
	a/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/scandinavian-showcase-with-an-irish
	-twist-presented-by-seattle-folklore-society-skandia/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
